(* README *)

1 - Description
    -----------

    T000 provides a mechanized proof of the pigeonhole divisibility theorem
    in Rocq.  The result states that any subset A of {1, ..., 2n} with
    |A| = n + 1 contains two distinct elements a and b such that a | b or
    b | a.

    The development relies only on the standard libraries Arith, Bool, Lia,
    List, and PeanoNat.  The proof factors into three parts: an odd-part
    decomposition sending each element of {1, ..., 2n} to one of n odd
    categories, a list-based pigeonhole argument producing two elements
    with the same odd part, and an arithmetic lemma showing that shared odd
    parts force divisibility.

    T000 is the canonical template package for Proofcase.  Its appendix/
    directory contains the extracted OCaml artifacts for the executable
    arithmetic surface, together with the Canonicalization note describing
    the packaging and naming conventions that later T### developments are
    expected to follow.


2 - Repository Tree
    ---------------

    .
    ├── README
    │
    │      (This file.)
    │
    ├── R01__Odd_Part.v
    │
    │      Odd-part decomposition of positive integers.  We define the
    │      odd_part and val2 functions, prove that odd_part is odd, divides
    │      the original input, and supports the decomposition
    │      n = 2^(val2 n) * odd_part n.  We also define odd_range n, the n
    │      odd numbers in {1, ..., 2n}, and show it has length n and
    │      receives every odd_part image from that interval.
    │
    ├── R02__Pigeonhole_Divisibility.v
    │
    │      Main theorem.  We state a list-based pigeonhole principle and
    │      apply it with the odd-part map to conclude that any
    │      (n+1)-element subset of {1, ..., 2n} contains a divisibility
    │      pair.
    │
    ├── T000__Comprehension.v
    │
    │      Audit-facing proof index for the public T000 surface:
    │      arithmetic normalization, finite odd-codomain control, the
    │      abstract pigeonhole principle, and the final divisibility
    │      endpoint.
    │
    ├── T000__Extraction_Interface.v
    │
    │      OCaml extraction surface for odd-part computations, odd-range
    │      inspection, finite witness search, and assumption reporting for
    │      the principal theorems.
    │
    └── appendix
           ├── Canonicalization
           │
           │      Canonical style memorandum for template-level Proofcase
           │      packaging: file naming, headers, imports, naming
           │      conventions, and structural organization.
           │
           ├── OddPartComputations.ml
           │
           │      Extracted OCaml implementation of the odd-part and 2-adic
           │      valuation computations, together with odd-range and
           │      profiling utilities.
           │
           ├── OddPartComputations.mli
           │
           │      Generated OCaml interface exposing the extracted odd-part
           │      computation surface.
           │
           ├── PigeonholeDivisibilityWitness.ml
           │
           │      Extracted OCaml implementation of finite witness search for
           │      same-odd-part collisions and divisibility classification.
           │
           └── PigeonholeDivisibilityWitness.mli
           
                  Generated OCaml interface for the extracted witness-search
                  surface.
